The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Three criminals shot at Prahlad Gupta, 35, the owner of a beauty parlour in Salkia, Howrah, around 7.15pm on Wednesday. Police said the trio entered Guptas shop and fired at him. Gupta came out of his shop and collapsed. Local traders rushed him to TL Jaiswal Hospital but he was later shifted to Medical College and Hospital, where his condition was said to be critical. The police suspect that Gupta knew the criminals but the motive for the attack is yet to be ascertained. 

 A passenger waiting to board a connecting flight to Delhi at Netaji Subash Chandra Bose International Airport died of a heart attack around 6pm on Tuesday. Sampat Sarkar, 55, was travelling to Delhi from Silchar with his teenaged son. He complained of severe chest pain while waiting for the flight. Airport employees were immediately informed but Sarkar was declared dead when the doctor arrived.

 A construction worker was injured after railings of a scaffolding collapsed at the Mani Square site, on the EM Bypass, around noon on Wednesday, according to a spokesperson for the Mani Group. The worker sustained multiple injuries from the fall, which was partially arrested by his harness belt. We have admitted him to Apollo Gleneagles Hospitals, he added.

 Union civil aviation minister Praful Patel will meet chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee on September 7 in the city to discuss the proposed modernisation of Calcutta airport. The state government will also declare the inauguration date for Behala Flying Club the same day. The Camellia Group will operate the club.

 All the councillors and former councillors will be granted free parking passes, according to mayor Bikash Ranjan Bhattacharyya on Wednesday. 

